title: LLAMA BENCHMARK [PY] 12/22/2025
content:
import streamlit as st
import pandas as pd
import subprocess
import os
import re
import datetime
import time

# ==========================================
# CONFIGURATION
# ==========================================
BASE_DIR = os.getcwd()
MODELS_DIR = os.path.join(BASE_DIR, "models")
LOGS_DIR = os.path.join(BASE_DIR, "bench_logs")
BENCH_EXE = os.path.join(BASE_DIR, "llama-bench.exe")
DB_FILE = os.path.join(BASE_DIR, "model_library_benchmark.csv")
KEYWORDS = ["NSFW", "Uncensored", "Amoral", "Dark", "Fallen", "Rivermind", "Snowpiercer", "Abyss", "Erebus", "Lewd"]

if not os.path.exists(LOGS_DIR):
    os.makedirs(LOGS_DIR)

# --- SCHEMA ---
COLS = [
    # Identity
    "Model_Name", "Size_GB", "Quant", "Role", "B_Tag", "Params_Actual", "Backend",
    # Metrics
    "Gen_TG128", "Gen_TG128_StDev", "Ingest_PP512", "Rating_Speed", 
    # Human Eval
    "HE_Overall", "HE_Math", "HE_Science", "HE_History", "HE_Music",
    "HE_English", "HE_Coding", "HE_Logic", "HE_Creative", "HE_RP_Quality", 
    "HE_Personality", "HE_Emotes", "HE_Formatting", "HE_Instructions", 
    "HE_Censorship", "HE_Memory", "HE_Summarize", "HE_Translation", 
    "HE_JSON", "HE_RAG", "HE_Vision", "HE_Fun_Factor"
]

st.set_page_config(page_title="Llama.cpp Librarian", layout="wide", page_icon="ü¶ô")

# ==========================================
# FUNCTIONS
# ==========================================
def get_hardware_info():
    try:
        gpu_info = subprocess.check_output("nvidia-smi --query-gpu=name,memory.total,memory.free --format=csv,noheader,nounits", shell=True).decode().strip()
        gpu_name, total_vram, free_vram = gpu_info.split(',')
        return f"{gpu_name} | VRAM: {free_vram.strip()}MB Free / {total_vram.strip()}MB Total"
    except:
        return "GPU Detection Failed"

def parse_model_properties(filename):
    name = filename
    try:
        size_gb = round(os.path.getsize(os.path.join(MODELS_DIR, filename)) / (1024**3))
    except:
        size_gb = 0
    
    role = "Specialized/NSFW" if any(k.lower() in name.lower() for k in KEYWORDS) else "General"
    
    quant = "Unknown"
    quants = ["Q8_0", "Q6_K", "Q5_K_M", "Q5_K_S", "Q5_0", "Q4_K_M", "Q4_K_S", "Q4_0", "IQ3", "Q2_K", "F16", "F32"]
    for q in quants:
        if q.lower() in name.lower():
            quant = q
            break
            
    b_tag = "Other"
    b_match = re.search(r'(\d+(?:\.\d+)?)B', name, re.IGNORECASE)
    if b_match:
        b_tag = b_match.group(0).upper()

    return size_gb, role, quant, b_tag

def run_benchmark(model_name):
    model_path = os.path.join(MODELS_DIR, model_name)
    cmd = [BENCH_EXE, "-m", model_path, "-t", "8", "-ngl", "999"]
    
    try:
        result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, encoding='utf-8')
        output = result.stdout
        
        # Log
        timestamp = datetime.datetime.now().strftime("%Y-%m-%d_%H-%M-%S")
        log_file = os.path.join(LOGS_DIR, f"{model_name}_{timestamp}.log")
        with open(log_file, "w", encoding="utf-8") as f:
            f.write(f"COMMAND: {' '.join(cmd)}\n")
            f.write("="*40 + "\n")
            f.write(output)
            f.write("\n" + "="*40 + "\n")
            f.write(result.stderr)
            
        # Parse
        pp_match = re.search(r'\|\s*pp512\s*\|\s*([0-9\.]+)\s*\+/-\s*([0-9\.]+)', output)
        tg_match = re.search(r'\|\s*tg128\s*\|\s*([0-9\.]+)\s*\+/-\s*([0-9\.]+)', output)
        
        if not pp_match: pp_match = re.search(r'\|\s*pp512\s*\|\s*([0-9\.]+)', output)
        if not tg_match: tg_match = re.search(r'\|\s*tg128\s*\|\s*([0-9\.]+)', output)

        pp_val = float(pp_match.group(1)) if pp_match else 0.0
        tg_val = float(tg_match.group(1)) if tg_match else 0.0
        tg_std = float(tg_match.group(2)) if tg_match and len(tg_match.groups()) > 1 else 0.0

        backend = "Unknown"
        if "CUDA" in output: backend = "CUDA"
        elif "ROCm" in output: backend = "ROCm"
        elif "Metal" in output: backend = "Metal"
        elif "CPU" in output and "CUDA" not in output: backend = "CPU"
        
        params = "Unknown"
        param_match = re.search(r'\|\s*([0-9\.]+)\s*B\s*\|', output)
        if param_match:
            params = f"{param_match.group(1)}B"

        return {
            "pp": pp_val, "tg": tg_val, "tg_std": tg_std, 
            "backend": backend, "params": params, "raw": output
        }
    except Exception as e:
        return {"error": str(e)}

def load_db():
    if not os.path.exists(DB_FILE):
        return pd.DataFrame(columns=COLS)
    try:
        df = pd.read_csv(DB_FILE)
        for col in COLS:
            if col not in df.columns:
                if col.startswith("HE_"): df[col] = 0
                elif col == "Rating_Speed": df[col] = "Untested"
                elif col == "Backend": df[col] = "-"
                elif col == "Params_Actual": df[col] = "-"
                else: df[col] = 0.0
        return df[COLS]
    except:
        return pd.DataFrame(columns=COLS)

def save_db(df):
    df.to_csv(DB_FILE, index=False)

# ==========================================
# MAIN UI
# ==========================================
st.title("ü¶ô Llama.cpp Command Center")
st.caption(get_hardware_info())

if "last_bench_time" not in st.session_state:
    st.session_state.last_bench_time = 0

df = load_db()

# Sidebar Actions
st.sidebar.header("Actions")
if st.sidebar.button("üîÑ Scan & Index Library"):
    if not os.path.exists(MODELS_DIR):
        st.error(f"Models folder not found at: {MODELS_DIR}")
    else:
        files = [f for f in os.listdir(MODELS_DIR) if f.endswith(".gguf") and "mmproj" not in f]
        new_rows = []
        for f in files:
            existing = df[df['Model_Name'] == f]
            if not existing.empty:
                row = existing.iloc[0].to_dict()
                for c in COLS:
                    if c not in row: row[c] = 0
            else:
                s, r, q, b = parse_model_properties(f)
                row = {c: 0 for c in COLS}
                row.update({
                    "Model_Name": f, "Size_GB": s, "Quant": q, "Role": r, "B_Tag": b,
                    "Gen_TG128": 0.0, "Ingest_PP512": 0.0, "Rating_Speed": "Untested",
                    "Backend": "-", "Params_Actual": "-"
                })
            new_rows.append(row)
        df = pd.DataFrame(new_rows)[COLS]
        save_db(df)
        st.sidebar.success(f"Indexed {len(new_rows)} models!")
        st.rerun()

# --- TABS ---
tab1, tab2, tab3, tab4 = st.tabs(["üìä Speed", "üìù Human Ratings", "‚öñÔ∏è Analysis & Winners", "üöÄ Benchmarking"])

with tab1:
    st.subheader("Speed Leaderboard")
    if not df.empty and df['Gen_TG128'].max() > 0:
        clean = df[df['Gen_TG128'] > 0].sort_values(by="Gen_TG128", ascending=False).head(15)
        st.bar_chart(clean, x="Model_Name", y="Gen_TG128", color="Quant")
        
        display_cols = ["Model_Name", "Params_Actual", "Backend", "Quant", "Gen_TG128", "Gen_TG128_StDev", "Rating_Speed"]
        st.dataframe(clean[display_cols], hide_index=True, width="stretch")
    else:
        st.info("No benchmarks run yet.")

with tab2:
    st.subheader("Human Ratings Matrix")
    st.info("Edit your scores (0-10) below. 'Overall' is auto-calculated when you Save.")
    
    if not df.empty:
        # Determine columns to edit (everything starting with HE_)
        he_cols = [c for c in COLS if c.startswith("HE_")]
        
        # Prepare Dataframe for Editor (Index = Model_Name to lock it)
        df_for_editing = df[["Model_Name"] + he_cols].set_index("Model_Name")
        
        edited_df = st.data_editor(
            df_for_editing, 
            key="human_eval_editor", 
            width="stretch",
            column_config={
                # Lock the Overall column so it's read-only
                "HE_Overall": st.column_config.NumberColumn("‚≠ê Overall (Auto)", format="%.1f", disabled=True),
            }
        )
        
        if st.button("üíæ Save & Calculate Averages"):
            # Update master DF from the edited version
            for model_name, row in edited_df.iterrows():
                master_idx = df.index[df['Model_Name'] == model_name]
                
                if not master_idx.empty:
                    # 1. Update the specific category columns
                    # We skip HE_Overall here because we calculate it below
                    for col in he_cols:
                        if col != "HE_Overall":
                            df.loc[master_idx, col] = row[col]
                    
                    # 2. AUTO-TABULATE LOGIC
                    # Extract the scores for this model
                    # We only want he_cols excluding overall
                    cat_scores = [row[c] for c in he_cols if c != "HE_Overall"]
                    
                    # Filter: Only count scores > 0 (Ignore "Unrated")
                    valid_scores = [s for s in cat_scores if s > 0]
                    
                    if valid_scores:
                        new_avg = sum(valid_scores) / len(valid_scores)
                    else:
                        new_avg = 0
                    
                    # 3. Write the calculated average
                    df.loc[master_idx, "HE_Overall"] = round(new_avg, 1)
            
            save_db(df)
            st.success("Saved! Overall scores have been updated.")
            time.sleep(1) # Brief pause for visual feedback
            st.rerun()    # Refresh page to show new numbers

with tab3:
    st.subheader("‚öñÔ∏è The Value Matrix (Speed vs. Smarts)")
    if df.empty or df['Gen_TG128'].max() == 0:
        st.warning("Please run benchmarks and add some human ratings to unlock this tab.")
    else:
        col_ctrl1, col_ctrl2 = st.columns([1, 2])
        with col_ctrl1:
            st.markdown("#### üéöÔ∏è Your Priorities")
            weight = st.slider("Preference Balance:", 0, 100, 50, format="%d%% Quality")
            w_qual = weight / 100.0
            w_speed = 1.0 - w_qual
            st.caption(f"Weights: Speed {int(w_speed*100)}% | Quality {int(w_qual*100)}%")

        adf = df.copy()
        max_speed = adf['Gen_TG128'].max()
        if max_speed == 0: max_speed = 1
        
        adf['Norm_Speed'] = adf['Gen_TG128'] / max_speed
        adf['Norm_Qual'] = adf['HE_Overall'] / 10.0
        adf['Win_Score'] = (adf['Norm_Speed'] * w_speed * 100) + (adf['Norm_Qual'] * w_qual * 100)
        winners = adf.sort_values(by="Win_Score", ascending=False)

        st.markdown(f"### üèÜ Top Models based on your {weight}% Quality Preference")
        winners['Win_Score'] = winners['Win_Score'].round(1)
        disp_cols = ["Model_Name", "Win_Score", "Gen_TG128", "HE_Overall", "Quant", "Size_GB"]
        
        st.dataframe(
            winners[disp_cols].head(15), 
            hide_index=True, 
            width="stretch",
            column_config={
                "Win_Score": st.column_config.ProgressColumn("Composite Score", format="%.1f", min_value=0, max_value=100),
                "Gen_TG128": st.column_config.NumberColumn("Speed (t/s)", format="%.1f"),
                "HE_Overall": st.column_config.NumberColumn("Quality", format="%.1f"),
            }
        )

with tab4:
    st.subheader("Benchmarking Station")
    if not df.empty:
        model = st.selectbox("Select Model", df['Model_Name'].unique())
        
        if st.button(f"üî• Run Benchmark: {model}"):
            now = time.time()
            if now - st.session_state.last_bench_time < 2.0:
                st.warning("‚è≥ Too fast!")
            else:
                st.session_state.last_bench_time = now
                with st.spinner("Running llama-bench..."):
                    data = run_benchmark(model)
                
                if "error" in data:
                    st.error(f"Failed: {data['error']}")
                else:
                    tg = data['tg']
                    rating = "SLOW üî¥"
                    if tg > 10: rating = "USABLE üü°"
                    if tg > 25: rating = "SMOOTH üü¢"
                    if tg > 50: rating = "GODLIKE üöÄ"
                    
                    st.success(f"Speed: {tg} t/s (¬±{data['tg_std']})")
                    
                    idx = df.index[df['Model_Name'] == model].tolist()[0]
                    df.at[idx, 'Gen_TG128'] = tg
                    df.at[idx, 'Gen_TG128_StDev'] = data['tg_std']
                    df.at[idx, 'Ingest_PP512'] = data['pp']
                    df.at[idx, 'Rating_Speed'] = rating
                    df.at[idx, 'Backend'] = data['backend']
                    df.at[idx, 'Params_Actual'] = data['params']
                    save_db(df)
                    
                    with st.expander("üìÑ View Raw Benchmark Output", expanded=True):
                        st.code(data['raw'], language="text")
                    st.caption(f"Log saved to: {LOGS_DIR}")
    else:
        st.warning("Library is empty.")

title: maxrw
content:
#!/bin/sh
#
# Find the maximum I/O size for a single read/write syscall
# Uses binary search after detecting the approximate limit by doubling
#
# Works on Linux, BSD, and other POSIX systems

set -eu

# Start with 1 MB
size=$((1024 * 1024))
prev_size=0

echo 'Finding maximum syscall I/O size...'
echo 'Starting from 1 MB and doubling until limit is reached'
echo

while true; do
	# Convert size to human-readable format
	if [ "$size" -lt $((1024 * 1024)) ]; then
		size_kb=$((size / 1024))
		size_str="$size_kb KB"
	elif [ "$size" -lt $((1024 * 1024 * 1024)) ]; then
		size_mb=$((size / 1024 / 1024))
		size_str="$size_mb MB"
	else
		size_gb=$((size / 1024 / 1024 / 1024))
		size_str="$size_gb GB"
	fi

	printf "Testing size: $size_str ... "

	# Read 'size' bytes in one syscall and count actual bytes read
	bytes_read=$(dd status=none if=/dev/zero count=1 bs="$size" | wc -c)

	# Check if we got fewer bytes than requested (short read)
	if [ "$prev_size" -gt 0 ] && [ "$bytes_read" -lt "$size" ]; then
		echo 'LIMIT REACHED'
		break
	fi

	echo OK

	# Save current size for next iteration
	prev_size=$size

	# Double the size for next iteration
	new_size=$((size * 2))

	# Check for overflow (when doubling causes a negative number or smaller value)
	if [ "$new_size" -le "$size" ]; then
		echo
		echo 'Reached maximum representable size without hitting limit'
		echo "Maximum tested size: $size bytes ($size_str)"
		exit 0
	fi

	size=$new_size
done

echo
echo "Starting binary search between $prev_size and $size bytes..."
echo

# Binary search for exact limit
low=$prev_size
high=$size
initial_high=$high

# Calculate human-readable format for initial_high
if [ "$initial_high" -lt $((1024 * 1024)) ]; then
	initial_high_kb=$((initial_high / 1024))
	initial_high_str="${initial_high_kb} KB"
elif [ "$initial_high" -lt $((1024 * 1024 * 1024)) ]; then
	initial_high_mb=$((initial_high / 1024 / 1024))
	initial_high_str="${initial_high_mb} MB"
else
	initial_high_gb=$((initial_high / 1024 / 1024 / 1024))
	initial_high_str="${initial_high_gb} GB"
fi

while [ $((high - low)) -gt 1 ]; do
	mid=$(((low + high) / 2))

	# Calculate how much we subtracted from initial_high
	subtracted=$((initial_high - mid))

	printf "  Trying $initial_high_str - $subtracted bytes ... "

	# Test if this size works - check if we get all bytes
	bytes_read=$(dd status=none if=/dev/zero count=1 bs="$mid" | wc -c)

	if [ "$bytes_read" -eq "$mid" ]; then
		echo OK
		low=$mid
	else
		echo FAIL
		high=$mid
	fi
done

echo
echo '======================================='
echo " MAXIMUM SYSCALL I/O SIZE: $low bytes"
echo '======================================='
echo "  Decimal: $low"
printf "  Hex:     0x%x\n" "$low"
echo

title: LLAMA BENCHMARK v10 [BATH] 12/22/2025

@echo off
SETLOCAL ENABLEDELAYEDEXPANSION
title Llama.cpp Librarian and Benchmark Tool v10

REM =========================================================
REM                  CONFIG & DEFAULTS
REM =========================================================
set "BASE=%~dp0"
set "MODELS_DIR=%BASE%models"
set "BENCH_DB=%BASE%model_library_benchmark.csv"
set "LLAMA_BENCH=%BASE%llama-bench.exe"

REM --- Keywords for Role Detection ---
set "KEYWORDS=NSFW Uncensored Amoral Dark Fallen Rivermind Snowpiercer Abyss Erebus Lewd Heretic"

REM Default Bench Settings
set THREADS=8
set GPU_LAYERS=999

REM =========================================================
REM           HARDWARE DETECTION
REM =========================================================
:GET_STATS
echo Detecting Hardware Context...

set "CPU_NAME=Unknown"
set "GPU_NAME=N/A"
set "VRAM_TOTAL_GB=0"
set "VRAM_FREE_GB=0"
set "RAM_TOTAL_GB=0"
set "DRIVER_VER=N/A"

REM --- CPU ---
for /f "skip=1 delims=" %%a in ('wmic cpu get name 2^>nul') do if not defined CPU_NAME set "CPU_NAME=%%a"
for /f "tokens=* delims= " %%a in ("%CPU_NAME%") do set "CPU_NAME=%%a"

REM --- RAM ---
for /f "skip=1" %%p in ('wmic os get TotalVisibleMemorySize') do if not defined RAM_RAW set "RAM_RAW=%%p"
set /a RAM_TOTAL_GB=%RAM_RAW%/1024/1024

REM --- GPU ---
nvidia-smi --query-gpu=name,memory.total,memory.free,driver_version --format=csv,noheader,nounits > "%BASE%gpu.tmp" 2>nul
if %errorlevel%==0 (
    for /f "tokens=1,2,3,4 delims=," %%a in ('type "%BASE%gpu.tmp"') do (
        set "GPU_NAME=%%a"
        set /a VRAM_TOTAL_GB=%%b/1024
        set /a VRAM_FREE_GB=%%c/1024
        set "DRIVER_VER=%%d"
    )
    del "%BASE%gpu.tmp"
)

REM =========================================================
REM                  MAIN MENU
REM =========================================================
:MAIN_MENU
cls
echo ========================================================
echo             LIBRARIAN AND BENCHMARK v10
echo ========================================================
echo  SYSTEM CONTEXT:
echo   GPU:  %GPU_NAME% (%VRAM_FREE_GB%GB / %VRAM_TOTAL_GB%GB)
echo   RAM:  %RAM_TOTAL_GB%GB System Memory
echo   Drv:  %DRIVER_VER%
echo ========================================================
echo.
echo  [1] Scan Library (Sorted by Size/Quant)
echo  [2] View Leaderboard (Top Speed)
echo  [3] View Full Database
echo  [4] Exit
echo.
set /p "CHOICE=Selection: "

if "%CHOICE%"=="1" goto :SCAN_MODELS
if "%CHOICE%"=="2" goto :LEADERBOARD
if "%CHOICE%"=="3" goto :VIEW_DB
if "%CHOICE%"=="4" exit
goto :MAIN_MENU

REM =========================================================
REM           INTELLIGENT SCANNING ENGINE
REM =========================================================
:SCAN_MODELS
cls
echo Indexing Library...
echo.

set count=0

REM --- Initialize CSV Header if missing ---
if not exist "%BENCH_DB%" (
    echo Model_Name,Size_GB,Quant,Role,Template_Guess,Fit_Status,Ingest_PP512,Gen_TG128,Rating,GPU,Date > "%BENCH_DB%"
)

for %%F in ("%MODELS_DIR%\*.gguf") do (
    set "fname=%%~nxF"
    set "fpath=%%F"
    
    echo !fname! | findstr /i "mmproj" >nul
    if !errorlevel! NEQ 0 (
        set /a count+=1
        
        REM --- 1. Size Calculation ---
        set "size_gb=0"
        for /f "usebackq" %%S in (`powershell -NoProfile -Command "[int][math]::Round(%%~zF / 1GB)"`) do set "size_gb=%%S"
        
        REM --- 2. Fit Analysis ---
        set "fit_status=Unknown"
        if !size_gb! LSS !VRAM_FREE_GB! (
            set "fit_status=GPU_FAST"
        ) else (
             set /a total_mem=!VRAM_FREE_GB! + !RAM_TOTAL_GB!
             if !size_gb! LSS !total_mem! (
                 set "fit_status=CPU_SPLIT"
             ) else (
                 set "fit_status=TOO_LARGE"
             )
        )

        REM --- 3. Role Detection ---
        set "role=General"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "%KEYWORDS%" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "role=Specialized/NSFW"

        REM --- 4. Template Heuristics ---
        set "tmpl=Unknown"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "llama-3 llama3 dark-nexus rivermind snowpiercer" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "tmpl=Llama3"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "mistral v0.1 v0.2 v0.3" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "tmpl=Mistral"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "chatml heremes dolphin yi looking-glass" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "tmpl=ChatML"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "alpaca" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "tmpl=Alpaca"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "vicuna" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "tmpl=Vicuna"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "gemma" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "tmpl=Gemma"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "qwen" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "tmpl=Qwen"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "olmo" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "tmpl=Olmo"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "phi" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "tmpl=Phi"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "glm" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "tmpl=GLM"

        REM --- 5. B-Parameter Tag (Reversed for Correctness) ---
        set "b_tag=Other"
        REM Loop from Smallest to Largest so exact matches overwrite partial matches
        REM e.g. "12B" will overwrite "1B" (from v1b)
        for %%B in (0.5B 1B 1.5B 2B 3B 4B 6B 7B 8B 9B 11B 12B 13B 14B 16B 20B 24B 27B 30B 32B 34B 70B 72B) do (
            echo !fname! | findstr /I "%%B" >nul
            if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "b_tag=%%B"
        )

        REM --- 6. Quantization Detection ---
        set "quant=Unknown"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "f32" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "quant=F32"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "f16" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "quant=F16"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "Q8_0" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "quant=Q8_0"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "Q6_K" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "quant=Q6_K"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "Q5_K_M" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "quant=Q5_K_M"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "Q5_K_S" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "quant=Q5_K_S"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "Q5_0" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "quant=Q5_0"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "Q4_K_M" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "quant=Q4_K_M"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "Q4_K_S" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "quant=Q4_K_S"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "Q4_0" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "quant=Q4_0"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "Q3_K_M" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "quant=Q3_K_M"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "IQ3" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "quant=IQ3"
        echo !fname! | findstr /I "Q2_K" >nul
        if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "quant=Q2_K"

        REM --- Store in Array ---
        set "m_name[!count!]=!fname!"
        set "m_path[!count!]=!fpath!"
        set "m_size[!count!]=!size_gb!"
        set "m_fit[!count!]=!fit_status!"
        set "m_role[!count!]=!role!"
        set "m_tmpl[!count!]=!tmpl!"
        set "m_quant[!count!]=!quant!"
        set "m_btag[!count!]=!b_tag!"
    )
)

if %count% EQU 0 (
    echo No models found.
    pause
    goto :MAIN_MENU
)

REM =========================================================
REM           NESTED SORT DISPLAY (Size -> Quant)
REM =========================================================
echo.
echo  ID   STATUS      QUANT     ROLE       MODEL
echo -------------------------------------------------------------

for %%S in (72B 70B 34B 32B 30B 27B 24B 20B 16B 14B 13B 12B 11B 9B 8B 7B 6B 4B 3B 2B 1.5B 1B 0.5B Other) do (
    call :PRINT_SIZE_GROUP "%%S"
)

echo.
echo [A] Benchmark ALL models
echo [B] Back to Menu
echo.
set /p "B_SEL=Select ID to benchmark (or A): "

if /I "%B_SEL%"=="B" goto :MAIN_MENU
if /I "%B_SEL%"=="A" goto :BENCH_ALL

if defined m_path[%B_SEL%] (
    call :RUN_BENCH "%B_SEL%"
    pause
    goto :SCAN_MODELS
)
goto :SCAN_MODELS

REM =========================================================
REM        HELPER: PRINT SIZE GROUP
REM =========================================================
:PRINT_SIZE_GROUP
set "size_found=0"
for /L %%i in (1,1,%count%) do (
    if "!m_btag[%%i]!"=="%~1" set "size_found=1"
)
if !size_found! EQU 1 (
    echo.
    echo --- %~1 CLASS MODELS ---
    for %%Q in (F32 F16 Q8_0 Q6_K Q5_K_M Q5_K_S Q5_0 Q4_K_M Q4_K_S Q4_0 Q3_K_M IQ3 Q2_K Unknown) do (
        for /L %%i in (1,1,%count%) do (
             if "!m_btag[%%i]!"=="%~1" (
                 if /I "!m_quant[%%i]!"=="%%Q" (
                     echo  [%%i] [!m_fit[%%i]!] [!m_quant[%%i]!] [!m_role[%%i]!] !m_name[%%i]!
                 )
             )
        )
    )
)
exit /b

REM =========================================================
REM                  BENCHMARK RUNNER (REGEX FIXED)
REM =========================================================
:BENCH_ALL
for /L %%i in (1,1,%count%) do (
    call :RUN_BENCH "%%i"
)
echo All tasks complete.
pause
goto :SCAN_MODELS

:RUN_BENCH
set "idx=%~1"
set "target_name=!m_name[%idx%]!"
set "target_path=!m_path[%idx%]!"
set "target_fit=!m_fit[%idx%]!"
set "target_quant=!m_quant[%idx%]!"
set "target_tmpl=!m_tmpl[%idx%]!"
set "target_role=!m_role[%idx%]!"
set "target_size=!m_size[%idx%]!"
set "target_btag=!m_btag[%idx%]!"

cls
echo ========================================================
echo  BENCHMARKING: %target_name%
echo ========================================================
echo  Class:    %target_btag%
echo  Quant:    %target_quant%
echo  Fit:      %target_fit%
echo --------------------------------------------------------

if exist "%BASE%bench_temp.txt" del "%BASE%bench_temp.txt"

REM Run llama-bench
"%LLAMA_BENCH%" -m "%target_path%" -t %THREADS% -ngl %GPU_LAYERS% > "%BASE%bench_temp.txt" 2>&1

type "%BASE%bench_temp.txt"

REM --- PARSING WITH POWERSHELL REGEX (ROBUST) ---
set "PP512=0"
set "TG128=0"

for /f "usebackq tokens=*" %%v in (`powershell -NoProfile -Command "$c = Get-Content '%BASE%bench_temp.txt' | Select-String '\|\s*pp512\s*\|\s*([0-9\.]+)'; if ($c) { $c.Matches.Groups[1].Value } else { '0' }"`) do set "PP512=%%v"

for /f "usebackq tokens=*" %%v in (`powershell -NoProfile -Command "$c = Get-Content '%BASE%bench_temp.txt' | Select-String '\|\s*tg128\s*\|\s*([0-9\.]+)'; if ($c) { $c.Matches.Groups[1].Value } else { '0' }"`) do set "TG128=%%v"

REM --- CALCULATE RATING ---
set "rating=SLOW"
for /f "tokens=1 delims=." %%n in ("!TG128!") do set "INT_TG=%%n"

if !INT_TG! GEQ 10 set "rating=USABLE"
if !INT_TG! GEQ 25 set "rating=SMOOTH"
if !INT_TG! GEQ 50 set "rating=GODLIKE"

echo.
echo  ================================
echo   SPEED RATING: %rating% (!TG128! t/s)
echo  ================================
echo.

REM Save to CSV
echo logging to %BENCH_DB%...
for /f "tokens=2 delims==" %%I in ('wmic os get localdatetime /value') do set datetime=%%I
set "TS=%datetime:~0,4%-%datetime:~4,2%-%datetime:~6,2%"

echo %target_name%,%target_size%,%target_quant%,%target_role%,%target_tmpl%,%target_fit%,!PP512!,!TG128!,%rating%,%GPU_NAME%,%TS% >> "%BENCH_DB%"

echo Done.
exit /b

REM =========================================================
REM                  LEADERBOARD
REM =========================================================
:LEADERBOARD
cls
echo ========================================================
echo                  SPEED LEADERBOARD
echo ========================================================
if not exist "%BENCH_DB%" (
    echo No database found. Please scan/benchmark first.
    pause
    goto :MAIN_MENU
)

echo.
echo TOP 15 FASTEST MODELS (Generation Speed):
echo -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
REM PowerShell magic with ErrorAction Ignore for bad data rows
powershell -NoProfile -Command ^
    "$data = Import-Csv '%BENCH_DB%';" ^
    "$clean_data = $data | Where-Object { $_.Gen_TG128 -match '^\d+(\.\d+)?$' };" ^
    "$sorted = $clean_data | Sort-Object -Property @{Expression={[double]$_.Gen_TG128}; Descending=$true};" ^
    "$sorted | Select-Object -First 15 Model_Name, Size_GB, Quant, Gen_TG128, Rating | Format-Table -AutoSize"

echo.
pause
goto :MAIN_MENU

REM =========================================================
REM                  VIEW DATABASE
REM =========================================================
:VIEW_DB
cls
if not exist "%BENCH_DB%" (
    echo Database not found.
    pause
    goto :MAIN_MENU
)
echo Opening Database in default CSV viewer...
start "" "%BENCH_DB%"
goto :MAIN_MENU

@echo off
SETLOCAL ENABLEDELAYEDEXPANSION
title Llama.cpp Configurable Launcher

REM =========================================================
REM                  GLOBAL DEFAULTS
REM =========================================================

set "BASE=%~dp0"
set "MODELS_DIR=%BASE%models"
set "EXE_NAME=llama-server.exe"

REM --- Browser Settings ---
set BROWSER_DELAY=0
set AUTO_OPEN_BROWSER=1

REM --- Hardware Settings (Global) ---
set PORT=8080
set HOST=127.0.0.1
set "GPU_LAYERS=999"
set "THREADS=8"
set "PARALLEL_SLOTS=1"

REM --- Model Keywords ---
set "KEYWORDS=NSFW Uncensored Amoral Dark Fallen Rivermind Snowpiercer Abyss Erebus Lewd"

REM =========================================================
REM                  SYSTEM STATS
REM =========================================================
:GET_STATS
set "CPU_USAGE=0"
set "RAM_INFO=0/0"
set "GPU_NAME=N/A"
set "GPU_INFO=0/0"
set "GPU_LOAD=0"
set "DRIVER_VER=N/A"
set "CUDA_VER=N/A"
set "PYTHON_VER=N/A"
set "LLAMA_VER=N/A"

REM --- Hardware ---
for /f "skip=1" %%p in ('wmic cpu get loadpercentage') do if not defined CPU_LOAD set "CPU_LOAD=%%p"
for /f "skip=1" %%p in ('wmic os get FreePhysicalMemory') do if not defined RAM_FREE set "RAM_FREE=%%p"
for /f "skip=1" %%p in ('wmic os get TotalVisibleMemorySize') do if not defined RAM_TOTAL set "RAM_TOTAL=%%p"
set /a RAM_TOTAL_GB=%RAM_TOTAL%/1024/1024
set /a RAM_USED_GB=(%RAM_TOTAL% - %RAM_FREE%)/1024/1024
set "RAM_INFO=%RAM_USED_GB%GB / %RAM_TOTAL_GB%GB"

nvidia-smi --query-gpu=name,utilization.gpu,memory.used,memory.total,driver_version --format=csv,noheader,nounits > "%BASE%gpu.tmp" 2>nul
if %errorlevel%==0 (
    for /f "tokens=1,2,3,4,5 delims=," %%a in ('type "%BASE%gpu.tmp"') do (
        set "GPU_NAME=%%a"
        set "GPU_LOAD=%%b"
        set "GPU_INFO=%%cMB / %%dMB"
        set "DRIVER_VER=%%e"
    )
    del "%BASE%gpu.tmp"
    nvidia-smi | findstr /C:"CUDA Version" > "%BASE%cuda.tmp"
    set /p CUDA_RAW=<"%BASE%cuda.tmp"
    for /f "tokens=9" %%x in ("!CUDA_RAW!") do set "CUDA_VER=%%x"
    del "%BASE%cuda.tmp"
)

REM --- Software ---
python --version > "%BASE%py.tmp" 2>&1
set /p PY_RAW=<"%BASE%py.tmp"
if not "%PY_RAW%"=="" set "PYTHON_VER=%PY_RAW%"
del "%BASE%py.tmp"

if exist "%BASE%%EXE_NAME%" (
    "%BASE%%EXE_NAME%" --version 2>&1 | findstr "build:" > "%BASE%llama.tmp"
    set /p LLAMA_RAW=<"%BASE%llama.tmp"
    if not "!LLAMA_RAW!"=="" set "LLAMA_VER=!LLAMA_RAW!"
    del "%BASE%llama.tmp"
)

REM =========================================================
REM                  MAIN MENU
REM =========================================================
:MAIN_MENU
cls
echo ========================================================
echo                 SYSTEM DASHBOARD
echo ========================================================
echo  HARDWARE:
echo   CPU: %CPU_LOAD%%% Load     RAM: %RAM_INFO%
echo   GPU: %GPU_NAME%
echo   MEM: %GPU_INFO%     Load: %GPU_LOAD%%%
echo.
echo  SOFTWARE:
echo   Llama:   %LLAMA_VER%
echo   Python:  %PYTHON_VER%
echo   NVIDIA:  Driver %DRIVER_VER% / CUDA %CUDA_VER%
echo ========================================================
echo.
echo  [1] Select Model and Launch
echo  [2] Refresh Stats
echo  [3] Edit Configuration
echo  [4] Exit
echo.
echo ========================================================
set /p "CHOICE=Enter selection (1-4): "

if "%CHOICE%"=="1" goto :MODEL_SELECT
if "%CHOICE%"=="2" goto :GET_STATS
if "%CHOICE%"=="3" goto :EDIT_CONFIG
if "%CHOICE%"=="4" exit
goto :MAIN_MENU

REM =========================================================
REM                  MODEL SELECTION
REM =========================================================
:MODEL_SELECT
cls
echo ========================================================
echo               AVAILABLE MODELS
echo ========================================================
echo Scanning...
echo.

set idx=0
set unc_count=0
set std_count=0

for /f "tokens=1 delims==" %%v in ('set f_path[ 2^>nul') do set "%%v="
for /f "tokens=1 delims==" %%v in ('set f_name[ 2^>nul') do set "%%v="

if not exist "%MODELS_DIR%" mkdir "%MODELS_DIR%"

for %%f in ("%MODELS_DIR%\*.gguf") do (
    set "fname=%%~nxf"
    set "fpath=%%f"
    set "is_unc=0"
    echo !fname! | findstr /I "%KEYWORDS%" >nul
    if !errorlevel! EQU 0 set "is_unc=1"
    if !is_unc! EQU 1 (
        set /a unc_count+=1
        set "unc_n[!unc_count!]=!fname!"
        set "unc_p[!unc_count!]=!fpath!"
    ) else (
        set /a std_count+=1
        set "std_n[!std_count!]=!fname!"
        set "std_p[!std_count!]=!fpath!"
    )
)

if %unc_count% EQU 0 if %std_count% EQU 0 (
    echo No models found. & pause & goto :MAIN_MENU
)

if %unc_count% GTR 0 (
    echo  --- SPECIALIZED / UNCENSORED ---
    for /L %%i in (1,1,%unc_count%) do (
        set /a idx+=1
        set "f_name[!idx!]=!unc_n[%%i]!"
        set "f_path[!idx!]=!unc_p[%%i]!"
        echo  [!idx!] !unc_n[%%i]!
    )
    echo.
)

if %std_count% GTR 0 (
    echo  --- STANDARD / GENERAL ---
    for /L %%i in (1,1,%std_count%) do (
        set /a idx+=1
        set "f_name[!idx!]=!std_n[%%i]!"
        set "f_path[!idx!]=!std_p[%%i]!"
        echo  [!idx!] !std_n[%%i]!
    )
)

echo.
echo ========================================================
set /p "M_SEL=Select model (1-%idx%): "
if "%M_SEL%"=="" goto :MODEL_SELECT
if %M_SEL% GTR %idx% goto :MODEL_SELECT
if %M_SEL% LSS 1 goto :MODEL_SELECT
set "SEL_PATH=!f_path[%M_SEL%]!"
set "SEL_NAME=!f_name[%M_SEL%]!"

REM =========================================================
REM             CHECK FOR SAVED CONFIG
REM =========================================================
:CHECK_CONFIG
set "CONFIG_FILE=%SEL_PATH%.llama_config.bat"

if exist "%CONFIG_FILE%" (
    call "%CONFIG_FILE%"
    goto :AUTO_LAUNCH_COUNTDOWN
)
goto :MANUAL_SETUP

REM =========================================================
REM             AUTO LAUNCH COUNTDOWN
REM =========================================================
:AUTO_LAUNCH_COUNTDOWN
cls
echo ========================================================
echo             SAVED CONFIG LOADED
echo ========================================================
echo Model:    %SEL_NAME%
echo Template: %CFG_TEMPLATE_NAME%
echo Context:  %CFG_CONTEXT%
echo Vision:   %CFG_VISION_NAME%
echo ========================================================
echo.
echo Launching in 3 seconds...
echo.
echo [ Press 'E' to Edit/Reset settings ]
echo [ Press 'SPACE' to Launch immediately ]
echo.

REM Choice command to handle key input with timeout
choice /C E /T 3 /D E /N >nul 2>&1
if %errorlevel%==1 goto :RESET_CONFIG
REM If timeout (which defaults to E choice in batch workaround, logic below fixes flow)

REM Actually, choice /T 3 /D Y (wait 3s, default Y). 
REM We use a simpler method: timeout allowing keypress
timeout /t 3
goto :LAUNCH_WITH_CONFIG

:RESET_CONFIG
cls
echo Resetting configuration for this model...
del "%CONFIG_FILE%"
goto :MANUAL_SETUP

:LAUNCH_WITH_CONFIG
REM Map the CFG variables to runtime variables
set "CONTEXT_SIZE=%CFG_CONTEXT%"
set "TEMPLATE_FLAG=%CFG_TEMPLATE_FLAG%"
set "MMPROJ_FLAG=%CFG_MMPROJ_FLAG%"
goto :LAUNCH

REM =========================================================
REM             MANUAL SETUP WIZARD
REM =========================================================
:MANUAL_SETUP
REM --- 1. Vision ---
cls
echo [SETUP 1/3] Vision / Multimodal
echo --------------------------------
echo Does %SEL_NAME% need a projector file?
echo.
echo [1] No (Standard)
echo [2] Yes (Select mmproj file)
echo.
set /p "V_CHOICE=Select (1-2): "
set "MMPROJ_FLAG="
set "CFG_VISION_NAME=None"

if "%V_CHOICE%"=="2" (
    cls
    echo Scanning for *mmproj*...
    set v_idx=0
    for /f "tokens=1 delims==" %%v in ('set v_path[ 2^>nul') do set "%%v="
    for %%f in ("%MODELS_DIR%\*mmproj*.gguf") do (
        set /a v_idx+=1
        set "v_path[!v_idx!]=%%f"
        echo [!v_idx!] %%~nxf
    )
    if !v_idx!==0 (
        echo No mmproj files found. Skipping.
        timeout /t 2 >nul
    ) else (
        echo.
        set /p "PROJ_SEL=Select file: "
        if defined v_path[!PROJ_SEL!] (
            set "MMPROJ_FLAG=--mmproj "!v_path[%PROJ_SEL%]!""
            set "CFG_VISION_NAME=Active"
        )
    )
)

REM --- 2. Template ---
cls
echo [SETUP 2/3] Chat Template
echo --------------------------------
echo [1] Auto-Detect (Standard)
echo [2] ChatML      (Alice, Uncensored, Dolphin)
echo [3] Llama 3     (Meta Llama 3)
echo [4] Mistral     (Mistral v0.1/0.3)
echo [5] Alpaca      (Older Merges)
echo.
set /p "T_SEL=Select (1-5): "
set "TEMPLATE_FLAG="
set "CFG_TEMPLATE_NAME=Auto"
if "%T_SEL%"=="2" (set "TEMPLATE_FLAG=--chat-template chatml" & set "CFG_TEMPLATE_NAME=ChatML")
if "%T_SEL%"=="3" (set "TEMPLATE_FLAG=--chat-template llama3" & set "CFG_TEMPLATE_NAME=Llama3")
if "%T_SEL%"=="4" (set "TEMPLATE_FLAG=--chat-template mistral" & set "CFG_TEMPLATE_NAME=Mistral")
if "%T_SEL%"=="5" (set "TEMPLATE_FLAG=--chat-template alpaca" & set "CFG_TEMPLATE_NAME=Alpaca")

REM --- 3. Context Size ---
cls
echo [SETUP 3/3] Context Size (Memory)
echo --------------------------------
echo [1] 8192  (Standard - Best for Q4/Q5 models)
echo [2] 4096  (Rescue Mode - Use if Q6/Q8 models crash/slow)
echo [3] 16384 (High - Needs lots of VRAM)
echo.
set /p "C_SEL=Select (1-3): "
set "CONTEXT_SIZE=8192"
if "%C_SEL%"=="2" set "CONTEXT_SIZE=4096"
if "%C_SEL%"=="3" set "CONTEXT_SIZE=16384"

REM --- SAVE CONFIG? ---
cls
echo ========================================================
echo                 CONFIGURATION READY
echo ========================================================
echo Model:    %SEL_NAME%
echo Template: %CFG_TEMPLATE_NAME%
echo Context:  %CONTEXT_SIZE%
echo Vision:   %CFG_VISION_NAME%
echo ========================================================
echo.
set /p "SAVE_CONF=Save as default for this model? (Y/N): "
if /I "%SAVE_CONF%"=="Y" (
    (
        echo set "CFG_CONTEXT=%CONTEXT_SIZE%"
        echo set "CFG_TEMPLATE_FLAG=%TEMPLATE_FLAG%"
        echo set "CFG_TEMPLATE_NAME=%CFG_TEMPLATE_NAME%"
        echo set "CFG_MMPROJ_FLAG=%MMPROJ_FLAG%"
        echo set "CFG_VISION_NAME=%CFG_VISION_NAME%"
    ) > "%CONFIG_FILE%"
    echo Config saved!
)

goto :LAUNCH

REM =========================================================
REM                  LAUNCH
REM =========================================================
:LAUNCH
cls
echo ========================================================
echo Launching...
echo Model: %SEL_NAME%
echo Mode:  %CONTEXT_SIZE% Context / %CFG_TEMPLATE_NAME%
echo ========================================================
echo.

if %AUTO_OPEN_BROWSER%==1 (
    if %BROWSER_DELAY% GTR 0 (
         echo Opening browser in %BROWSER_DELAY%s...
         timeout /t %BROWSER_DELAY% /nobreak >nul
    )
    start http://%HOST%:%PORT%
)

"%BASE%%EXE_NAME%" ^
    -m "%SEL_PATH%" ^
    --host %HOST% ^
    --port %PORT% ^
    -c %CONTEXT_SIZE% ^
    -ngl %GPU_LAYERS% ^
    -t %THREADS% ^
    -np %PARALLEL_SLOTS% ^
    %TEMPLATE_FLAG% ^
    %MMPROJ_FLAG%

echo.
echo Server closed.
pause
goto :GET_STATS

:EDIT_CONFIG
cls
echo.
echo Please right-click this batch file and select "Edit".
echo.
pause
goto :GET_STATS
